(24, 1, '2020-06-17 11:41:41', '2020-06-17 11:41:41', '<div class=\"content-box\">\r\nContents\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#aadhaar\">What is aadhaar ?</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#download\">How  to download aadhaar ?</a></li>\r\n</ul></div>\r\n<h2 id=\"aadhaar\">What is aadhaar?</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aadhaar is the largest biometric identification scheme in the world. World Bank CEO Paul Romer described Aadhaar as \"the world\'s most sophisticated ID system.\" Aadhaar has been the target of many decisions by India\'s Supreme Court. The Supreme Court released an interim order on 23 September 2013 saying that \"no-one will suffer for not getting Aadhaar\". Adding that, since it is voluntary and not mandatory, the government can not deny a service to a resident who does not own Aadhaar. It is a 12-digit unique identification number that residents or passport holders of India can voluntarily obtain based on their biometric and demographic data. The data is collected by the Unique Indian Identification Authority (UIDAI), a statutory authority founded by the Government of India in January 2009 under the jurisdiction of the Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology, under the provisions of the Aadhaar Act (Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services), 2016</span>\r\n\r\n<h2 id=\"download\">How to Download aadhaar?</h2>\r\n<b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Having an e-Aadhaar card keeps your Aadhaar information handy and eliminates the possibility that you will ever lose or forget your Aadhaar number. It is appropriate across the country as it is a digital version of your standard Aadhaar, without exceptions.</span> </b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Aadhaar Card Info', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-06-17 11:41:41', '2020-06-17 11:41:41', '', 11, 'http://localhost/aadhaar-card-info/2020/06/17/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
