(69, 1, '2020-06-19 11:15:38', '2020-06-19 11:15:38', 'Having an <strong>e-Aadhaar</strong> card keeps your Aadhaar information handy and eliminates the possibility that you will ever lose or forget your Aadhaar number. It is appropriate across the country as it is a <strong>digital version</strong> of your <strong>standard Aadhaar</strong>, without exceptions.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-63 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/aadhaar-card-info/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Download.png\" alt=\"download-aadhaar-number-virualid\" width=\"2240\" height=\"1260\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Download Via Aadhaar Number</strong></h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Visit the official Aadhar website https:/uidai.gov.in/</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on the My Aadhaar choice ‘Download Aadhaar’ button or visit the https:/eaadhaar.uidai.gov.in / link</li>\r\n 	<li>Choose “Aadhaar” choice under section “I Have”</li>\r\n 	<li>Enter the Aadhaar number 12-digit now. If you want to download Masked Aadhaar click on ‘I want a masked Aadhaar’ link.</li>\r\n 	<li>Enter the Captcha Verification Code and press the “Return OTP” option to get your registered mobile number with the one time password</li>\r\n 	<li>Enter the OTP your mobile number has received.</li>\r\n 	<li>Complete the survey, and press “Verify and Install” to access your Aadhaar’s electronic file</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2><strong>Download </strong><b>Via Virtual ID\r\n</b></h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Visit the Indian Unique Identification Authority (UIDAI) official web site.</li>\r\n 	<li>Tap tab \'My Aadhaar\'</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on the link \'download aadhaar\' under the tab \'Get aadhaar\'</li>\r\n 	<li>A new tab opens. Under \'I have\' line, pick \'Digital ID\' choice.</li>\r\n 	<li>Type your 16 digits Virtual ID number (VID) and verification code captcha as shown on the page.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click \'OTP submit\' button.</li>\r\n 	<li>On your registered mobile phone or email address, you will obtain a one-time password (OTP)</li>\r\n 	<li>To check your request enter the OTP obtained on your mobile phone. Then click the \'Call and Download\' button</li>\r\n 	<li>You can access your e-aadhaar card successfully in PDF format after validation, which is protected by a password.</li>\r\n 	<li>Enter the password when you open your e-aadhaar PDF document (as per the instructions given)</li>\r\n 	<li>You now have your e-aadhaar card which you can print for reference.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'How to download aadhaar card ? | Using aadhaar number / virtual id', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '66-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-06-19 11:15:38', '2020-06-19 11:15:38', '', 66, 'http://localhost/aadhaar-card-info/2020/06/19/66-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
